[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:30,350 --> 00:01:35,950
[Our Interpreter]

3
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:39,009
[Episode 23]

4
00:01:39,890 --> 00:01:41,750
[Stars have been shining in the sky]

5
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:43,240
[for tens of millions of years.]

6
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,090
[They stare at each other,]

7
00:01:45,090 --> 00:01:48,310
[full of the pain of love.]

8
00:01:48,310 --> 00:01:51,310
[They talk to each other.]

9
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:57,410
[Those words are so elegant and meaningful.]

10
00:01:57,410 --> 00:02:00,910
[But no scholar in the world]

11
00:02:00,910 --> 00:02:03,730
[can understand them.]

12
00:02:03,730 --> 00:02:07,510
[Heinrich Heine]

13
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:16,950
Train me?

14
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:19,150
Don't sugarcoat it.

15
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:20,750
This is workplace bullying.

16
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:22,190
Lin Xi.

17
00:02:23,350 --> 00:02:25,030
Have you ever thought

18
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:27,829
that I don't want to be successful?

19
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:29,360
I just want

20
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,020
a comfortable bed

21
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:33,470
on which I can have a good sleep.

22
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,870
But that's impossible!

23
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:36,030
Stop pretending

24
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,160
like you care for me.

25
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:38,630
Do you think that in Huasheng,

26
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:39,880
I'm the only one who hates you?

27
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,300
Do you know that almost everyone in the company

28
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,829
doesn't like you?

29
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:53,160
Are you still thinking about Chen Wen?

30
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:00,550
I'm thinking

31
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:02,890
that maybe I was wrong too.

32
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:09,120
You shouldn't have put her in an important position.

33
00:03:11,070 --> 00:03:12,110
I shouldn't

34
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:13,590
have forced

35
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:14,910
my beliefs

36
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,070
on her.

37
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:19,070
Why?

38
00:03:23,390 --> 00:03:24,710
Does she want

39
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:26,230
what I want?

40
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:28,870
Is what I think is good

41
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,790
also good in her eyes?

42
00:03:32,950 --> 00:03:35,030
Does she also want to pursue

43
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:36,110
what I pursued

44
00:03:36,950 --> 00:03:38,430
eight years ago?

45
00:03:40,510 --> 00:03:41,190
No.

46
00:03:44,670 --> 00:03:46,829
What she wants is simple.

47
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:49,070
She just wishes

48
00:03:49,070 --> 00:03:50,200
to have a good sleep.

49
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:55,320
Stop thinking about it.

50
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:58,150
Am I a failure?

51
00:03:58,430 --> 00:03:59,910
This is not your fault.

52
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:07,870
Although

53
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:10,510
I know very well

54
00:04:10,530 --> 00:04:12,390
that I'm not an easygoing person,

55
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:14,150
I didn't expect

56
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,790
that so many people disliked me,

57
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:17,850
found me annoying,

58
00:04:18,269 --> 00:04:20,230
and even hated me.

59
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:24,590
My subordinate wanted to set me up.

60
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:25,870
Other people

61
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:27,770
just stood by and watched.

62
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:39,440
Stop thinking about it.

63
00:04:40,790 --> 00:04:41,630
It's okay.

64
00:04:45,590 --> 00:04:47,390
I need to recharge my batteries.

65
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:52,110
Come with me.

66
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:59,700
[One more time]

67
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:05,190
What are you doing?

68
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:07,310
It'll soon be October 1st.

69
00:05:07,310 --> 00:05:09,070
A trip with me can get your mind off it.

70
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,670
Here. Choose a destination.

71
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,070
No need.

72
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:18,810
I've got a travel plan.

73
00:05:20,630 --> 00:05:22,310
Y-You've got a travel plan?

74
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:24,110
Who are you going to travel with?

75
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:25,310
Do I know them?

76
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:30,790
You're going to travel

77
00:05:30,790 --> 00:05:31,830
with people I don't know?

78
00:05:31,830 --> 00:05:32,870
Are they men or women?

79
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:33,670
How many are they?

80
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:34,470
Who are they?

81
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:37,909
Enough.

82
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,030
Good night.

83
00:05:41,590 --> 00:05:43,110
See you next week.

84
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:46,030
Next week?

85
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:47,909
Wait.

86
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:56,310
How many guys will there be?

87
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:57,030
Xixi.

88
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,670
After learning that you're coming back,

89
00:05:58,670 --> 00:05:59,670
your dad worked in the field

90
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:00,990
the whole afternoon.

91
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:01,990
He said

92
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,620
he'd prepare the freshest

93
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:05,230
seasonal vegetables for you.

94
00:06:05,230 --> 00:06:06,470
Lin.

95
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:07,790
Just because your arthritis

96
00:06:07,790 --> 00:06:09,310
has gotten better recently

97
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:10,750
doesn't mean you can wear yourself out.

98
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:12,190
I've told him off.

99
00:06:12,470 --> 00:06:14,110
I told him that you were living in a big city

100
00:06:14,110 --> 00:06:15,870
where you could buy any kind of food.

101
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:17,510
That's different.

102
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,310
I planted those vegetables myself.

103
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:24,760
[Mic on] [Speaker on] [Camera on]

104
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:20,390
I'll wash them myself

105
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:21,670
and cook them myself for you.

106
00:06:21,670 --> 00:06:22,950
It's the special treatment

107
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:24,080
for my dear daughter

108
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:25,030
and your mom.

109
00:06:25,030 --> 00:06:25,710
The two of you

110
00:06:25,710 --> 00:06:26,710
will always get special treatment

111
00:06:26,710 --> 00:06:27,710
from me.

112
00:06:28,710 --> 00:06:30,300
Don't imagine we'll be touched.

113
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:30,950
Lin.

114
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:37,950
[Mic on] [Speaker on] [Camera on]

115
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:32,950
You can ask our daughter.

116
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:33,510
Dear.

117
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:34,830
When you were in school,

118
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:35,950
you had the most loving dad

119
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:37,510
in your class, didn't you?

120
00:06:38,030 --> 00:06:40,310
You were the most doting dad.

121
00:06:40,590 --> 00:06:49,750
[Mic on] [Speaker on] [Camera on]

122
00:06:40,870 --> 00:06:42,230
If Xixi never got married,

123
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:43,690
would that make you happy?

124
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,270
Yes.

125
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:46,060
Very happy.

126
00:06:46,670 --> 00:06:47,470
If you can't find

127
00:06:47,470 --> 00:06:48,750
a man better than me,

128
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,030
you might as well just stay single.

129
00:06:50,030 --> 00:06:50,750
Am I right?

130
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:53,620
What are you talking about?

131
00:07:10,950 --> 00:07:12,430
What's your plan

132
00:07:12,430 --> 00:07:13,350
for the National Day Golden Week?

133
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,150
I'll join you.

134
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,110
You don't even know

135
00:07:17,110 --> 00:07:17,710
where I'm going.

136
00:07:17,710 --> 00:07:19,510
It doesn't matter. I'm not picky.

137
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:20,640
Where are you going?

138
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:22,730
Are you sure you want to go with me?

139
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:23,630
Yes.

140
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,010
Okay. Come with me.

141
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:40,150
Nice view.

142
00:07:43,310 --> 00:07:45,390
Is this place newly developed?

143
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:48,880
Not really. It's been like this for years.

144
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,950
You should've told me about your plan,

145
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:53,950
so I wouldn't have searched online

146
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,409
for tourist attractions.

147
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:01,350
Don't turn at this intersection.

148
00:08:01,350 --> 00:08:02,670
Turn at the next intersection.

149
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:03,800
There's a shortcut.

150
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:08,270
You're quite familiar with this place.

151
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:10,870
Of course. This is the way to my parents' house.

152
00:08:12,350 --> 00:08:13,830
Why didn't you tell me?

153
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:16,430
You didn't ask.

154
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:17,910
You said it didn't matter,

155
00:08:17,910 --> 00:08:19,170
and you were not picky.

156
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:20,720
I didn't prepare anything.

157
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:25,080
Then what do you say? You want to turn back?

158
00:08:39,270 --> 00:08:40,070
Wait for me in the car.

159
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:41,130
I'll be right back.

160
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:51,510
Madam.

161
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:52,670
I'd like to know

162
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:53,990
what the most expensive wine is

163
00:08:53,990 --> 00:08:54,440
in your store.

164
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,350
Do you have Moutai?

165
00:08:55,350 --> 00:08:57,070
Moutai is too expensive for such a small store.

166
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:58,790
We have homemade wine.

167
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:01,270
Homemade wine?

168
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:03,590
It won't work.

169
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:05,630
Young man.

170
00:09:05,630 --> 00:09:06,670
What do you mean?

171
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:09,470
I'm going to visit my future parents-in-law.

172
00:09:09,470 --> 00:09:10,990
I can't send them your homemade wine

173
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:11,830
as a gift.

174
00:09:12,230 --> 00:09:13,230
Look over there.

175
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:14,670
They are

176
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:20,840
[Wenli Products]

177
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:16,430
products from a local ecological farm.

178
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:18,030
All the locals know that brand.

179
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:19,870
They're great gifts

180
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:20,910
for your future parents-in-law.

181
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:22,100
They'll surely approve of your marriage.

182
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:27,600
[Wenli Products]

183
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,440
Really?

184
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,110
Yes.

185
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:25,290
I do hope they will.

186
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:26,750
I'll buy one of each kind.

187
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:27,670
-Sure.
-How much?

188
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:28,550
290 yuan.

189
00:09:28,590 --> 00:09:29,070
Okay.

190
00:09:36,690 --> 00:09:39,860
[Organic Oranges]

191
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,560
You've bought gifts?

192
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:58,650
I bought some local specialties.

193
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:05,190
How do I look today?

194
00:10:06,470 --> 00:10:07,390
Great.

195
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:10,350
What's wrong?

196
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:11,980
Mr. Xiao,

197
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:13,630
you're a man of the world.

198
00:10:13,710 --> 00:10:15,590
Why are you nervous now?

199
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,830
I'm not nervous.

200
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:18,890
I just don't go to battle unprepared.

201
00:10:19,470 --> 00:10:20,830
It's a small village.

202
00:10:20,950 --> 00:10:22,430
You don't need to make any preparations.

203
00:10:22,430 --> 00:10:23,630
That's different.

204
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:26,070
I'm going to meet your parents.

205
00:10:26,310 --> 00:10:27,640
I have to be thoughtful.

206
00:10:29,310 --> 00:10:30,240
My dad

207
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,310
is just a farmer.

208
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:33,600
He works in the field every day.

209
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,390
What you wear

210
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:35,650
doesn't matter to him.

211
00:10:35,830 --> 00:10:37,560
But your mom is well-educated.

212
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:40,190
That's already in the past.

213
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:41,150
Now,

214
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:43,680
she's just an English teacher in the village.

215
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:48,510
After you meet my parents,

216
00:10:48,510 --> 00:10:50,110
just don't look down on them.

217
00:10:51,110 --> 00:10:52,510
Why would I possibly do that?

218
00:10:52,510 --> 00:10:54,240
No matter what your parents do,

219
00:10:54,310 --> 00:10:55,950
I'll deeply respect them.

220
00:10:58,110 --> 00:10:59,150
Besides,

221
00:10:59,150 --> 00:10:59,790
I'll bring

222
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,910
AI agricultural technology

223
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:01,830
to this place

224
00:11:02,710 --> 00:11:03,870
to change

225
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:05,390
the backward lifestyle of the countryside.

226
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:06,830
That's the least I can do.

227
00:11:10,710 --> 00:11:11,350
Let's go.

228
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:52,850
[Peach Blossom Village]

229
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:49,110
Xixi.

230
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,170
You didn't have to do this.

231
00:11:51,990 --> 00:11:52,790
Do what?

232
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,310
I mean,

233
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:55,150
you didn't have to arrange for me

234
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:55,830
to meet your parents

235
00:11:55,830 --> 00:11:57,150
at a resort.

236
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:59,150
I didn't arrange anything.

237
00:12:00,310 --> 00:12:01,710
Then where is this place?

238
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,580
[Peach Blossom Village]

239
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,900
This is where my parents live.

240
00:12:06,470 --> 00:12:08,230
All right. Let's get our luggage.

241
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:08,740
Okay.

242
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:12,290
[Peach Blossom Village]

243
00:12:12,290 --> 00:12:14,460
[Organic Strawberries]

244
00:12:15,310 --> 00:12:16,230
Xiao Yicheng.

245
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:19,830
These are the local specialties you bought?

246
00:12:20,430 --> 00:12:21,270
Yes.

247
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:22,890
You think they're improper?

248
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:27,590
I don't know if they're too proper

249
00:12:27,590 --> 00:12:29,430
or too improper.

250
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:30,530
How about this?

251
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:31,750
Leave them here.

252
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:32,670
We won't take them with us.

253
00:12:32,670 --> 00:12:33,870
Are there any gift shops nearby?

254
00:12:33,870 --> 00:12:34,630
I'll go buy other gifts.

255
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:35,310
This is my first time…

256
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:36,190
No, no, no.

257
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:37,830
They'll like whatever you bought.

258
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:38,690
Just take them.

259
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,790
Let me do it.

260
00:12:59,580 --> 00:13:00,590
Why didn't you

261
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:02,070
tell me in advance?

262
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:03,870
I didn't prepare anything.

263
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:05,230
It's a surprise.

264
00:13:05,390 --> 00:13:06,630
What surprise?

265
00:13:06,630 --> 00:13:08,090
Mom, let me introduce him.

266
00:13:08,590 --> 00:13:10,470
This is my boyfriend, Xiao Yicheng.

267
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:11,270
Hello, Mrs. Lin.

268
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:12,030
I'm Xiao Yicheng.

269
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:13,110
Hello.

270
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:14,190
Have a seat.

271
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:14,850
Have a seat.

272
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:15,510
You too.

273
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:15,990
Have a seat.

274
00:13:15,990 --> 00:13:17,470
I told your dad you were home.

275
00:13:17,470 --> 00:13:18,720
He's on his way back.

276
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:19,510
I know.

277
00:13:19,510 --> 00:13:20,640
I sent him a message.

278
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,260
-Xixi.
-Sit.

279
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:23,120
Xixi.

280
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:25,090
-Where are you, Xixi?
-He's back.

281
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:26,470
Xixi.

282
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:28,710
Xixi.

283
00:13:28,710 --> 00:13:29,350
Xi…

284
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:30,710
Lin!

285
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:33,270
My dear daughter,

286
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:34,030
you're finally back.

287
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:35,190
I missed you so much.

288
00:13:35,190 --> 00:13:35,950
Let me look at you.

289
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:37,310
Let me introduce someone to you.

290
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:37,790
Come.

291
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:40,030
He's Xixi's boyfriend.

292
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:40,750
Nice to meet you, Mr. Lin.

293
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,080
My name is Xiao Yicheng.

294
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:43,030
My daughter

