-Thank you, Mrs. Lin.

303
00:13:58,470 --> 00:13:59,600
Thank you, Mrs. Lin.

304
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:01,430
Thank you.

305
00:14:06,990 --> 00:14:07,710
Wenli.

306
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,410
You brought them here?

307
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,350
No.

308
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,590
I bought them.

309
00:14:12,350 --> 00:14:13,870
You bought them for me?

310
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:16,480
Well,

311
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,310
I came in a hurry this time.

312
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,620
I couldn't find better gifts

313
00:14:19,620 --> 00:14:20,710
in the town.

314
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:21,790
They're indeed not suitable gifts.

315
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:22,750
Not suitable?

316
00:14:23,350 --> 00:14:25,070
So you think these things

317
00:14:25,070 --> 00:14:26,030
are bad?

318
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:33,870
Yes. They're indeed not good enough.

319
00:14:33,870 --> 00:14:35,670
They're indeed not good enough?

320
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:38,510
Then tell me

321
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:39,880
what's wrong with them.

322
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,230
I mean, I don't know

323
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:45,790
what you two like.

324
00:14:45,910 --> 00:14:47,550
I came in a hurry.

325
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:49,350
Sorry that I didn't come

326
00:14:49,350 --> 00:14:50,410
with better gifts.

327
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:54,310
You should be sorry.

328
00:14:56,110 --> 00:14:57,390
Enough. Enough.

329
00:14:57,830 --> 00:14:59,190
Cut him some slack.

330
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:00,950
There are so many things in the store,

331
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:01,910
but he chose

332
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:03,070
to buy our products.

333
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:04,800
Isn't it a lovely coincidence?

334
00:15:04,990 --> 00:15:06,270
It's good.

335
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:07,350
Yes.

336
00:15:08,430 --> 00:15:09,990
Let me explain it to you.

337
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:12,070
My mom's name is Gao Wenli.

338
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:13,840
Wenli

339
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:14,850
[Wenli Ecological Farm]

340
00:15:14,390 --> 00:15:16,390
is the brand of our ecological farm.

341
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:24,190
Is this

342
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:26,280
also from your parents' brand?

343
00:15:27,710 --> 00:15:29,310
I used to drink it very often.

344
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:33,750
Xixi.

345
00:15:34,110 --> 00:15:35,830
Be honest with me.

346
00:15:35,830 --> 00:15:38,000
I want to hear the truth.

347
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:39,710
What do your parents do?

348
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:42,990
They run an ecological farm

349
00:15:43,190 --> 00:15:45,110
and sell local specialties.

350
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:45,870
That's it?

351
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:48,590
They also run a hotel.

352
00:15:48,830 --> 00:15:50,070
They found a designer

353
00:15:50,070 --> 00:15:51,510
to design these villas.

354
00:15:51,510 --> 00:15:53,190
We keep several rooms to ourselves.

355
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:54,650
The rest are for tourists.

356
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,710
The rest?

357
00:15:56,710 --> 00:15:57,790
What else?

358
00:15:59,430 --> 00:16:01,030
Other than that,

359
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,550
there are also

360
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:04,070
related small businesses here and there.

361
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:04,990
Small businesses?

362
00:16:04,990 --> 00:16:06,030
Like what?

363
00:16:06,030 --> 00:16:07,110
You can't equivocate this time.

364
00:16:07,110 --> 00:16:07,910
Make it clear.

365
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:11,230
Come here.

366
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:19,390
Everything you can see from here

367
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:20,390
belongs to my dad.

368
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:24,470
I was trying so hard to raise funds.

369
00:16:24,470 --> 00:16:26,070
I should've just come to you.

370
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:29,350
Mr. Xiao, you didn't tell me you needed money.

371
00:16:29,350 --> 00:16:30,990
You didn't tell me your dad was so rich.

372
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:33,190
I didn't think it was worth mentioning.

373
00:16:34,430 --> 00:16:35,990
I always thought…

374
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:39,150
You thought

375
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:39,910
my mom

376
00:16:39,910 --> 00:16:40,990
eloped with a penniless guy?

377
00:16:40,990 --> 00:16:42,190
I didn't say that.

378
00:16:42,190 --> 00:16:44,070
You implied that.

379
00:16:44,780 --> 00:16:46,350
I didn't lie.

380
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:48,110
My dad

381
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:49,150
was just a diligent

382
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:50,480
farmer.

383
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:52,310
If I remember correctly,

384
00:16:52,310 --> 00:16:53,710
my dad's business got better

385
00:16:53,710 --> 00:16:55,630
when I was in high school.

386
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:57,720
Thanks to the favorable policies.

387
00:16:58,910 --> 00:17:00,310
Do you think I'll buy that?

388
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:01,590
You're fooling me again.

389
00:17:01,590 --> 00:17:03,150
I'm telling you the truth.

390
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:05,270
And my parents' lives

391
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,589
haven't changed much.

392
00:17:06,589 --> 00:17:07,920
My mom still teaches at the village school.

393
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:09,720
My dad is still a loving husband.

394
00:17:11,230 --> 00:17:11,990
I think

395
00:17:11,990 --> 00:17:13,550
your father is not only a loving husband

396
00:17:13,550 --> 00:17:14,640
but also a doting father.

397
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,700
You made me so embarrassed this time.

398
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:18,390
I have a bad feeling

399
00:17:18,589 --> 00:17:20,319
that I'll have a hard time here.

400
00:17:20,630 --> 00:17:22,230
You won't.

401
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:28,190
What does she see in him?

402
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:31,310
What on earth

403
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:32,920
does Xixi see

404
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:33,920
in that young man?

405
00:17:34,910 --> 00:17:36,510
That guy impressed me

406
00:17:36,510 --> 00:17:37,240
as a good man.

407
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,110
He has good manners.

408
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:44,190
Manners?

409
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:46,840
What's the use of having good manners?

410
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,830
Can one feed on manners?

411
00:17:51,190 --> 00:17:52,240
He has to be a man

412
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,630
who's down-to-earth

413
00:17:53,630 --> 00:17:55,750
and can make something of himself.

414
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:58,510
I heard he has a good job.

415
00:17:58,790 --> 00:18:00,980
I think he's well-paid.

416
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:02,440
I don't care about that.

417
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:03,750
Do we need money?

418
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:05,590
What we need

419
00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:07,650
is a son-in-law as outstanding as me.

420
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:13,270
Wenli.

421
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:14,470
You know,

422
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:16,470
I always do things your way.

423
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:17,660
This time,

424
00:18:17,870 --> 00:18:19,350
can we do it my way?

425
00:18:20,830 --> 00:18:21,710
If that young man

426
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:22,470
wants to marry

427
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:23,500
our daughter,

428
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:24,950
he has to

429
00:18:24,950 --> 00:18:26,810
go through me, Lin Dayong, first.

430
00:18:30,190 --> 00:18:31,650
Fine. Let's do it your way.

431
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:32,840
Here. Have some tea.

432
00:18:40,670 --> 00:18:41,110
Here.

433
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:41,870
-Thank you.
-Try this.

434
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:43,000
Have some yourself.

435
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:46,910
Can you drink?

436
00:18:47,990 --> 00:18:48,510
I...

437
00:18:48,510 --> 00:18:49,370
He can't drink.

438
00:18:52,350 --> 00:18:53,430
Try this too.

439
00:18:54,710 --> 00:18:55,550
Xiao.

440
00:18:55,950 --> 00:18:57,390
How do you like the food here?

441
00:18:57,390 --> 00:18:58,590
It's great, Mrs. Lin.

442
00:18:59,150 --> 00:19:00,230
Then eat up.

443
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:02,830
You don't like these dishes?

444
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:03,470
I do.

445
00:19:03,470 --> 00:19:05,310
I just don't eat a lot.

446
00:19:06,150 --> 00:19:08,100
You can't drink, and you eat like a bird.

447
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:09,100
I don't think

448
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:09,790
you're much better

449
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:10,870
in other aspects.

450
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,150
Mr. Lin.

451
00:19:16,430 --> 00:19:17,230
Mr. Lin.

452
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:19,360
Mrs. Gao. They're here.

453
00:19:19,630 --> 00:19:20,780
They're all here.

454
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:22,390
Who's here?

455
00:19:24,510 --> 00:19:25,630
Follow me.

456
00:19:26,150 --> 00:19:27,310
Come on. Come on.

457
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:34,990
Mrs. Gao. Dayong.

458
00:19:34,990 --> 00:19:35,710
Hurry.

459
00:19:36,790 --> 00:19:37,670
We're here.

460
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:38,710
Uncle.

461
00:19:38,710 --> 00:19:39,390
Hello, everyone.

462
00:19:39,390 --> 00:19:41,550
Wenqiang. Lin.

463
00:19:41,550 --> 00:19:42,510
You all came.

464
00:19:42,510 --> 00:19:43,110
Yes.

465
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:44,030
Great.

466
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:44,790
Lin.

467
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:45,620
What's in that pot?

468
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:46,390
Braised pork.

469
00:19:46,390 --> 00:19:47,340
It's freshly cooked.

470
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:48,230
Dayong.

471
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:49,270
I heard from Wang

472
00:19:49,270 --> 00:19:50,630
that your future son-in-law is here.

473
00:19:50,630 --> 00:19:52,150
So we all came.

474
00:19:52,150 --> 00:19:53,590
He's not my future son-in-law.

475
00:19:53,590 --> 00:19:54,470
Just a friend

476
00:19:54,470 --> 00:19:55,590
of Xi.

477
00:19:55,740 --> 00:19:56,460
He has to be her friend

478
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:57,990
before he becomes her husband.

479
00:19:57,990 --> 00:19:59,750
We have to uphold the tradition.

480
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:00,270
Yes.

481
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:00,990
We can't break from tradition.

482
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:01,920
What tradition?

483
00:20:01,990 --> 00:20:03,190
It's the local custom

484
00:20:03,190 --> 00:20:03,790
in Peach Blossom Village

485
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:05,550
to offer a guest

486
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:06,990
all the delicious food we have.

487
00:20:06,990 --> 00:20:08,070
Yes, young man.

488
00:20:08,110 --> 00:20:09,820
It's the local custom for a man

489
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:11,390
to eat as much as he can

490
00:20:11,390 --> 00:20:12,510
to show his affection

491
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:14,440
for a woman during his first visit.

492
00:20:14,470 --> 00:20:15,270
Really?

493
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:15,950
Yes.

494
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:16,750
Okay.

495
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,830
Serve the dishes.

496
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:19,830
Serve the dishes. Let's go.

497
00:20:31,310 --> 00:20:32,550
Scholar Cake.

498
00:20:37,630 --> 00:20:38,690
What are you doing?

499
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:43,470
The next dish is a roast chicken.

500
00:21:29,910 --> 00:21:31,150
Enough. Stop eating.

501
00:21:31,150 --> 00:21:32,110
Lin.

502
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,150
Next dish.

503
00:21:33,150 --> 00:21:33,790
Enough.

504
00:21:38,710 --> 00:21:39,960
Take the rest of the dishes home

505
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,490
and enjoy them yourselves.

506
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:43,510
Mr. Lin, I can keep eating.

507
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:44,630
I don't think you can.

508
00:21:44,630 --> 00:21:45,870
Are you trying to prove

509
00:21:45,870 --> 00:21:47,550
your love for Xixi by eating?

510
00:21:48,470 --> 00:21:49,790
What can that prove?

511
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,190
What do you mean?

512
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:53,990
My dad means

513
00:21:53,990 --> 00:21:55,110
you can stop eating.

514
00:21:55,110 --> 00:21:55,770
Look at you.

515
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:57,150
You haven't even married him

516
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:58,880
but are already defending him.

517
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:00,670
Folks,

518
00:22:00,910 --> 00:22:01,830
back then,

519
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:03,850
when I pursued Xixi's mom,

520
00:22:04,070 --> 00:22:05,190
I tried my best

521
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:06,310
to prove my love for her.

522
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:08,110
Why don't you tell him how I did it?

523
00:22:08,110 --> 00:22:08,670
Okay.

524
00:22:08,710 --> 00:22:10,910
Dayong is very handy.

525
00:22:10,950 --> 00:22:11,950
Yes.

526
00:22:11,950 --> 00:22:13,190
When Dayong and Wenli

527
00:22:13,190 --> 00:22:14,030
got married,

528
00:22:14,030 --> 00:22:14,630
he made their cabinet

529
00:22:14,630 --> 00:22:15,990
all by himself.

530
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:17,510
Things are different now.

531
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:18,230
Back then,

532
00:22:18,230 --> 00:22:19,460
you were too poor to buy furniture.

533
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:20,790
Was that about money?

534
00:22:21,350 --> 00:22:22,670
That was the way

535
00:22:22,910 --> 00:22:24,310
I showed my true affection to your mom.

536
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:25,110
Understand?

537
00:22:25,310 --> 00:22:26,190
Mr. Lin.

538
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:27,440
My love for Xixi

539
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:28,390
is true as well.

540
00:22:28,470 --> 00:22:29,600
I don't believe you.

541
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:31,150
You have to prove it

542
00:22:31,150 --> 00:22:32,910
to change my opinion of you.

543
00:22:34,430 --> 00:22:35,110
Okay.

544
00:22:35,550 --> 00:22:36,630
Then tell me

545
00:22:36,830 --> 00:22:37,950
what I should do

546
00:22:37,950 --> 00:22:39,010
to earn your trust.

547
00:22:39,910 --> 00:22:41,720
If you can make a handmade sofa,

548
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:42,630
I'll consider

549
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:43,590
marrying Xixi to you.

550
00:22:43,590 --> 00:22:44,990
Lin, you must be joking.

551
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:46,070
How can he make a sofa?

552
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:46,790
Where are the materials?

553
00:22:46,790 --> 00:22:48,110
There's a large bamboo forest behind the house.

554
00:22:48,110 --> 00:22:49,110
He can cut bamboo to make it.

555
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:49,950
Is that hard?

556
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:52,240
Okay.

557
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:53,710
Deal.

558
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:54,870
I can do it.

559
00:23:00,780 --> 00:23:02,310
[Indigestion Medicine]

560
00:23:05,910 --> 00:23:06,830
Xixi.

561
00:23:07,030 --> 00:23:08,070
Your dad

562
00:23:08,070 --> 00:23:09,350
actually cares about him.

563
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:10,830
Folks, let's go.

564
00:23:10,830 --> 00:23:11,980
Let's have some tea.

565
00:23:12,150 --> 00:23:12,580
Let's go.

566
00:23:12,580 --> 00:23:13,350
Eat it now.

567
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:15,190
Lin.

568
00:23:15,190 --> 00:23:15,920
I'm stuffed.

569
00:23:16,030 --> 00:23:17,630
Let's go upstairs for tea.

570
00:23:29,390 --> 00:23:30,310
Dayong.

571
00:23:31,070 --> 00:23:32,430
Why did you ask Xiao Yicheng

572
00:23:32,430 --> 00:23:33,750
to make a sofa?

573
00:23:34,550 --> 00:23:36,210
I don't think it's a good idea.

574
00:23:37,310 --> 00:23:38,110
Wenli.

575
00:23:38,910 --> 00:23:40,710
Xixi also thinks it's a bad idea.

576
00:23:40,870 --> 00:23:42,670
Can't you understand me either?

577
00:23:49,670 --> 00:23:50,430
Fine.

578
00:23:51,190 --> 00:23:53,340
I'll give you a chance to explain.

579
00:23:56,630 --> 00:23:58,430
When we were first together,

580
00:23:58,870 --> 00:24:00,390
I told you

581
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:02,550
I'd never

582
00:24:02,790 --> 00:24:04,430
let you suffer in your life.

583
00:24:04,430 --> 00:24:05,350
I promised to give you

584
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:06,510
a happy life.

585
00:24:06,830 --> 00:24:07,870
Do you remember that?

586
00:24:07,870 --> 00:24:08,790
Yes.

587
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:10,120
Of course I remember it.

588
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:13,080
You've fulfilled all your promises to me.

589
00:24:14,070 --> 00:24:15,350
I'm not

590
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:16,870
well-educated.

591
00:24:17,270 --> 00:24:18,340
My hands

